defaultPsychosocial disability is the preferred term used in the UN Convention on the Rights of Persons with Disabilities
default (
defaultCRPD
default)
default and defines people who are affected by a variety of mental health issues. Psychosocial disability does not represent any particular condition or category of mental disorder or illness, but is defined by the impact on a person’s life of the interaction of 
defaulta mental condition and the way that society treats that person as a consequence. 
default The Movement for Global Mental Health is 
defaulta network made up of service users, practitioners, academics, the development
default 
defaultcommunity and other stakeholders
default, which 
defaulthas
default a common 
defaultaim of advocating for protection of human rights and campaigning for improved access to appropriate mental health care
default. 
defaulthttp://www.globalmentalhealth.org/
default 
defaultOne DALY can be thought of as one lost year of "healthy" life. The sum of these DALYs across the 
defaultpopulation, or the burden of disease, can be thought of as a measurement of the gap between current health status and an ideal health situation where the entire population lives to an advanced age, free of disease and disability.
